<section class="report-page"><div class="report-inner"><header class="report-header"><h1>Days 61-90 | Prove one run</h1><img src="assets/brand/universal-orlando-logo.png" alt="Universal Orlando Resort"></header><section class="report-section"><h2>Objective</h2><p>Use one bounded, meaningful workflow to prove the operating system - not to declare enterprise transformation complete.</p><h2>Selection criteria</h2><div class="report-grid-3"><div class="report-card"><h3>Consequential enough</h3><p>A real guest, service or operating outcome with a named owner.</p></div><div class="report-card"><h3>Bounded enough</h3><p>Clear workflow, data sources, authority and manageable dependency surface.</p></div><div class="report-card"><h3>Measurable enough</h3><p>A baseline, leading indicators and an evidence window.</p></div></div><h2>Execution sequence</h2><ol><li>Baseline the workflow and define the outcome.</li><li>Document data lineage, model role, human authority and privacy/security boundaries.</li><li>Build or adapt the smallest useful intervention.</li><li>Run SIT, E2E, regression, performance and failure-recovery testing appropriate to risk.</li><li>Instrument model, system, workflow, adoption and economic signals.</li><li>Train operators and leaders; exercise override, escalation and rollback.</li><li>Issue a release, limited release, hold, rollback or retire disposition.</li></ol><h2>Evidence package</h2><p>Technical results, workflow change, adoption behavior, incident/fallback performance, benefits evidence, unresolved risks and reusable assets.</p><h2>Exit conditions</h2><div class="report-grid-2"><div class="report-card"><h3>Advance</h3><p>Outcome moves, controls hold, users retain the behavior and the run remains observable.</p></div><div class="report-card"><h3>Revise</h3><p>Value remains plausible but one or more Scene, Cue, Run or Review conditions need repair.</p></div><div class="report-card"><h3>Hold</h3><p>Evidence, authority, data quality or resilience is insufficient for broader exposure.</p></div><div class="report-card"><h3>Retire</h3><p>The case cannot justify its cost, consequence, adoption burden or dependency risk.</p></div></div></section><footer class="page-footer"><span>Russell Dudek | 120-day entry plan</span><span>4</span></footer></div></section>
<section class="report-page"><div class="report-inner"><header class="report-header"><h1>Days 91-120 | Compound the learning</h1><img src="assets/brand/universal-orlando-logo.png" alt="Universal Orlando Resort"></header><section class="report-section"><h2>Objective</h2><p>Convert the first run into better portfolio decisions, reusable technical assets and stronger internal capability.</p><div class="report-grid-2"><div class="report-card"><h3>Platform</h3><p>Harvest reusable data, deployment, observability, evaluation, security and recovery patterns.</p></div><div class="report-card"><h3>Portfolio</h3><p>Re-score adjacent cases using actual evidence; stop weak work and fund stronger repetitions.</p></div><div class="report-card"><h3>People</h3><p>Turn observed gaps into hiring, coaching, role clarity and community-of-practice priorities.</p></div><div class="report-card"><h3>Partners</h3><p>Translate incidents and evidence into vendor expectations, API SLOs, data rights, exit paths and commercial leverage.</p></div></div><h2>Day-120 outputs</h2><ul><li>Published enterprise AI roadmap grounded in current evidence and decision rights.</li><li>Prioritized staffing and capability plan.</li><li>Reusable production patterns and documented exceptions.</li><li>Executive scorecard with benefits, run-state, trust and adoption.</li><li>Next two production candidates and explicit stop/hold decisions.</li><li>Quarterly operating review and incident-learning cadence.</li></ul><h2>Day-120 executive review</h2><table class="phase-table"><tr><th>Review item</th><th>Decision sought</th></tr><tr><td>Portfolio evidence</td><td>Fund, sequence, constrain, hold or stop the next set of work.</td></tr><tr><td>Platform patterns</td><td>Standardize the reusable elements and name acceptable exceptions.</td></tr><tr><td>People and capacity</td><td>Approve hiring, development and ownership changes.</td></tr><tr><td>Partner posture</td><td>Strengthen SLOs, data rights, portability, fallback and commercial terms.</td></tr><tr><td>Learning agenda</td><td>Select the next assumptions and failure modes the portfolio must test.</td></tr></table><div class="callout">The first 120 days should leave Universal with a clearer system for making AI decisions - not simply a longer list of use cases.</div></section><footer class="page-footer"><span>Russell Dudek | 120-day entry plan</span><span>5</span></footer></div></section></main></body></html>